modules.description: Initializes a hash context with an optional key and specified output size, updates it with byte data, and produces a hash. Operates on byte buffers and produces fixed-size hash values. Computes hashes directly from input buffers without explicit context management.

Calculates BLAKE2 hash values using fixed-size output lengths and customizable parameters. Operates on byte sequences and provides a seeded hashing interface. Used to generate secure message digests for data integrity checks and cryptographic authentication.

Computes cryptographic hashes using the Blake2 algorithm, supporting key-based and keyless hashing with customizable output lengths. Processes byte sequences directly, handling context internally and returning fixed-size hash values. Supports incremental updates and single-pass hashing through unified interface. Can generate secure hashes for data verification, authentication, or fingerprinting.
